The paper discusses gradient-based algorithms for machine learning tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses statistical physics to analyze the behavior of these algorithms, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the presence of spurious local minima and the search for global minima, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
